Feb 21st 2018, there was a ‘possible gas leak’ or something similar outside Taylors townhouse at 153 Franklin st.

yes, its old news but its so interesting to me that i never knew about this until now.

anyways the photo from her renovation plans show the sidewalk where the incident (or whatever it was) occurred. i couldn’t really find anything in the plans that mentions that cover or what is there which is interesting because i imagine her renovations would affect that part of the sidewalk/road especially since she’s putting in a curb cut. and also interestingly, the photo from the plans was taken only a few days before gas leak. or whatever it was. idk.

tags: that last line gave me goosebumps
summary: But the best moments were when Swift dialed down the gimmicks and showed us her singer-songwriter soul. Backed only by her own...
text:
But the best moments were when Swift dialed down the gimmicks and showed us her singer-songwriter soul. Backed only by her own acoustic guitar, 22 reminded us that while Swift will never have the biggest voice in pop, she has one of the clearest and most communicative ones.

Amid all the pyrotechnics and insert-Sydney-here stage banter, that four minutes alone was worth the price of admission.

reblog.comment: Micheal Bailey, Sydney Morning Herald
